# Writer Improvement Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p2e1qe"
revision
=
fixing
spelling
only
```

or:

```text id="u7e6qe"
first draft
=
final draft
```

Some may think:

```text id="c4e8qe"
editing
=
rewriting
everything
```

without understanding:

```text id="k9e5qe"
revision
changes
ideas
and
organization
```

while:

```text id="n1e7qe"
editing
improves
correctness
```

Students may also:

```text id="t6e3qe"
avoid
rereading
their writing
```

Example:

student writes:

```text id="q5e2qe"
Dogs are fun.
```

and revises only:

```text id="v8e6qe"
dogs
→
Dogs
```

instead of strengthening ideas:

```text id="a7e8qe"
Dogs are fun
because
they provide
companionship
and exercise.
```

because:

```text id="g2e4rx"
revision
improves
meaning
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="v1e8rt"
writing improvement
through reflection
```

